ellcrafting..</span><hr size=1> Ok I've seen a lot of templates going around.  One thing to keep in mind is that imbue points are more important than the actual item stats (whether you prefer hps or cha for instance).  With SC you have a lot of leeway, and its always better to squeeze all those imbue points in early on.<br>
<br>
Here is one template (mine is actually different since I possess a summoners cloak, 41 imbue) that utilizes jewelcraft.<br>
---------------------<br>
Battlesung Gloves<br>
str 18 dex 15 energy 10 body 8<br>
<br>
avernal necklace (DF purchased, better than jcrafts best)<br>
heat 10 energy 10 con 19<br>
<br>
flamewrought ring (Malm drop, jcraft should make it identical or even irrelevant)<br>
dex/qui9 heat/spir 8<br>
<br>
infernal black diamond jewel (DF purchase, better than jcrafts best)<br>
str18 cold/body 10<br>
<br>
wow cloak (equivalent to jcraft highest item)<br>
str13/con13 cold/heat 8<br>
<br>
Then assuming you are 2h weapon, you have 6 spots open <br>
<br>
slot 1: 16 con, 9 spirit, 5 body, +3 weapon <br>
slot 2: hp 76, 11 thrust, 5 str, +1 weapon <br>
slot 3: hp 44, 11 crush, 5 thrust, +2 weap <br>
slot 4: hp 76, 9thrust, 9 slash, +1 weap <br>
slot 5: 17 dex, 19 cha, 9 qui, +1 weap <br>
slot 6: 15 dex, 9 matter, 9 crush, +1 weap <br>
<br>
Slot 4 requires 35 imbue points (overcharge your 100qua weapon), the rest are 31-32 imbue (overcharging 99qua material) <br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
Finally with jewelcrafting, one has a ring slot, 2 bracer slots, and a belt slot<br>
-----------------------------------------------------<br>
slot1<br>
con 28, str 22, energy 5, axe 1  (is =30)<br>
<br>
slot2<br>
+9 spirit, 19dex, resists 7 crush, parry+1 (is =2<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
slot3 <br>
11 slash, 5cold, 16cha, parry1 (is=2<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
slot4<br>
5slash, 16cha, 11matter, axe1 (is = 2<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
With that template everything is capped except<br>
<br>
hp-4, energy1, body-3, cold1, cha-22, 6 matter, 1 slash, parry-9, qui~-50.<br>
=========================================<br>
Note...  With an uber item like the GG cloak or summoners cloak, you basically get an additional 13 imbue.  With a legion hauberk, you get basically an additional 9 imbue.  With a ring of spun silk (quest drop in next patch), add 3 imbue.  With each additional masterpiece, add 3 imbue.  A flame wrought ring also can be jewelcrafted, maybe for an additional 2 imbue.  <br>
<br>
I have a Doden's bracer that is like 35 imbue.  I've heard as high as 38 drop.<br>
<br>
It should be clear that with some farming/money making, that capping cha, hitpoints, body and reducing parry to say -5 is doable.<br>
<br>
We have a lot of room to work with.  I'd say the only three things that are absolutely indispensable for a skald template to begin with is<br>
<br>
infernal black diamond jewel (str18 cold/body 10<br>
<br>
avernal necklace (heat 10 energy 10 con 19) <br>
<br>
and keeping our gloves.   These items are easy to procur, and unmakable with anything SC or Jewelcrafting could ever hope for.<br>
